no.motif.iter

Class PreparedIterable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.motif.iter.PreparedIterable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements in the iterable.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<T>, Appendable<T>, Elements<T>, Existance<T>, Filterable<T>, Mappable<T>, Prependable<T>, Reducible<T>, YieldsJavaCollection<T>

    public class PreparedIterable<T>
extends Object
implements Elements<T>, Serializable
    This class wraps an arbitrary Iterable and provides access to various operations to view and/or transform the wrapped iterable.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • collectIn

        public final <C extends Collection<T>> C collectIn(C collection)
        Description copied from interface: YieldsJavaCollection
        Collects the elements in this iterable in the given collection. The caller is responsible for supplying an appropriate collection implementation for what behavior that is expected. Keep in mind that sets does not allow duplicates, and many implementations also does not maintain the order of the elements. The collection must obviously support the add(..) operation. Unless you have particular needs for the resulting collection, consider using the YieldsJavaCollection.collect() method instead.
        Specified by:
        collectIn in interface YieldsJavaCollection<T>
        Parameters:
        collection - The collection to add the elements to.
        Returns:
        the given collection is returned.
